This legislation mirrors Oregon’s framework and will also ensure tipped workers are paid the same as non-tipped workers. It has been ten years since Congress raised the federal minimum wage and the time is now.

A $7.25 federal minimum wage is indefensible in this day and age. This week, I co-sponsored legislation introduced by Congresswoman Terri A. Sewell to raise the federal minimum wage to $15/hour in our nation’s cities and take a regional approach in less urban areas.
